<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 93 / Liberal Democrats at Torquay: Steel leads calls for UN
reform
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LIBERAL Democrats backed a call by Sir David Steel, the party's foreign
affairs spokesman, for a shake-up in the structure of the United Nations.
Delegates agreed there should be reform of the permanent membership of the
UN security council, but rejected a proposal requiring automatic seats for
the European Community and Japan.
A motion calling for the UN to develop peacemaking as well as peacekeeping
machinery was endorsed as was the establishment of an international criminal
court with a human rights commissioner within the UN.
Sir David said: 'We must ensure that the UN itself is fully accountable for
its actions or inactions.'
