FT  23 SEP 93 / Vodafone steps up phone price war
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
VODAFONE, the leading cellular mobile telephone operator, yesterday
announced a 50 per cent cut in peak-time rates for its new MetroDigital
service as the price war in the industry intensified, Paul Taylor writes.
It also unveiled an interest-free loan scheme which will enable customers to
spread the Pounds 240 cost of MetroDigital phones over two years.
The moves signal Vodafone's determination to compete head-to-head with
Mercury's new One-2-One digital service which is initially limited to within
the M25 area.
MetroDigital will initially be available in 168 cities and towns.
Subscribers will be able to nominate the location of their 'home cell' with
peak-time local calls costing 10p a minute and nationwide calls at 12.5p -
half existing tariffs. All off-peak calls will cost 5p a minute from the
home cell.
Lex, Page 18
