FT  22 SEP 93 / International Company News: IBM on offensive against Intel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
INTERNATIONAL Business Machines yesterday launched the initial volley in an
offensive to crack Intel's grip on the market for microprocessors used in
personal computers, writes Frank McGurty.
IBM has introduced a line of computers equipped with a new generation of
microprocessor, known as the PowerPC, developed over the past two years in
collaboration with Motorola and Apple Computer. The company hopes that the
PowerPC, which adapts IBM's existing RS/6000 technology for use in 'a
desktop personal computing environment', will eventually displace Intel's
microprocessors as the industry standard.
In what may prove a more important step towards that goal, IBM has begun
shipping the new chip to outside computer manufacturers, including Groupe
Bull of France.
