<HEADLINE>
FT  22 SEP 93 / World Trade News: Thai refinery financing deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rayong Refinery has signed Dollars 1.5bn of project financing facilities to
fund a hydrocracking refinery to be built in Thailand, writes Tracy
Corrigan. The total project cost will be about Dollars 2.4bn (Pounds
1.55bn).
Rayong Refinery is a joint venture owned by the Royal Dutch/Shell group (64
per cent) and the Petroleum Authority of Thailand (36 per cent).
The debt financing is made up of a Dollars 1.1bn facility, Dollars 425m of
which is expected to be supported by export credit political risk
guarantees; a Dollars 25m revolving credit facility; and a Dollars 375m
export credit loan from the Export-Import Bank of the US, which will be
guaranteed by three Thai banks.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Rayong Refinery.
</CO>
