FT  21 SEP 93 / Italy party accused over tax
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ITALY'S Party of the Democratic Left (PDS) has been embarrassed by
revelations that it failed to declare some L400m (Dollars 260,000) to the
tax authorities on a property deal.
The discovery led to the imprisonment over the week-end of Mr Marco Fredda,
in charge of property at the PDS, and Mr Primo Greganti, a former official
of the party when it was the Italian Communist Party (PCI).
This is the first time the PDS is accused of being involved in illicit party
financing. PDS officials have insisted no illegal party financing is at
stake like that of the other main parties.
However, the admission the party had knowingly kept funds which should have
been declared to the tax authorities has shown the PDS as anxious as the
rest to maximise its revenues.
